-- South Africa Gold Index Heads for 3-Month Low, Led by Harmony, Gold Fields
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2012-01-20T07:15:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/south-africa-gold-index-heads-for-3-month-low-led-by-harmony-gold-fields.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  Gold Mining
Index headed for its lowest level in three months, led by
declines in Harmony Gold Mining Co. and  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)   The five-member index dropped as much as 2.3 percent to
2,817.71, its lowest on a closing basis since Oct. 21, and was
trading at 2,823.65 of 9:06 a.m. in Johannesburg. Harmony,
Africaâ€™s third largest producer of the metal, lost 3.3 percent
to 90.40 rand. Gold Fields slipped 2.9 percent to 122.47 rand
and  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) , the biggest African producer of
gold, declined 1.4 percent to 345.98 rand.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
